# Write unit tests

- One unit (function, method, class) per test file; **arrange / act / assert** layout.
- Pure: no real network, real database, or shared filesystem (use temp dirs / in-memory).
- Mock or stub at boundaries you don't own; never mock the unit under test.
- Cover happy path, **boundary**, and **error** cases; one behavior per test.
- Name tests `<unit> <does X> when <condition>` (or the framework's equivalent).
- Tests must be deterministic—no time, randomness, or order dependence.
- Keep them fast: a unit suite should run in seconds, not minutes.
